BlueNext Proposes to Launch ‘Green’ Spot CERs, Excluding HFC-23

-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 
2011-05-09T13:14:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-09/bluenext-proposes-to-launch-green-spot-cers-excluding-hfc-23.html
BlueNext, the carbon exchange in
Paris, proposed to launch a new  spot market  in “green”
Certifed Emission Reduction credits and Emission Reduction Units
on May 13.  The market would exclude credits from cutting
hydrofluorocarbon-23 and nitrous oxide from adipic acid
production, both of which will be banned by the European Union
starting May 2013, according to an e-mailed statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mathew Carr in London at 
 m.carr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Verdonck at 
 rverdonck@bloomberg.net  